## Take action only on `trigger`, emit `done` or `err`
Buffers are impure, so you need pulses to keep order of execution correct.
```
void evaluate(Context ctx) {
  // only act on trigger, inputs not relevant for "dirty"
  if ( !isInputDirty<input_trigger>(ctx) ) return;

  if ( something is wrong ) {
    emitValue<output_ERR>(ctx, 1);
  }
  else {
    ...do your thing...
    emitValue<output_done>(ctx, 1); // did it
  }    

    ....
}
```

