## If you have an `output-buffer1`, always emit it
If you don't emit it, it will be NULL, which could confuse chained nodes.
If you follow this protocol, you don't have to worry that `buffer1` is null.

```
void evaluate(Context ctx) {
    ...

    auto buffer1 = getValue<input_buffer1>(ctx);

    ....

    // always fall through to do this:
    emitValue<output_buffer>(ctx, buffer1);
}
```

